<main role="main" class="content" id="main" tabindex="-1">
	<div id="level1">

		<article>

			<div id="content-top"></div>

			
			<header class="article-header">

												<div class="series-header">
					<p class="series-title"><a href="https://www.propublica.org/series/too-broke-for-bankruptcy"><span class="a11y">Series: </span>Too Broke for Bankruptcy</a></p>
									</div>
                
				<h2 class="hed">Many People are Too Broke for Bankruptcy. A New Report Suggests Some Fixes.</h2>
								<p class="dek">For many people, filing for bankruptcy is a luxury that’s out of reach. A new report by the primary bankruptcy professional organization is full of recommendations that, if implemented, could help change that.</p>
								<div class="metadata">
					<p class="byline">by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/paul-kiel">Paul Kiel</a></p>
					<time class="timestamp" datetime="2019-04-15EDT05:00">April 15, 2019, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
				</div>

								
<nav class="story-tools semi-fixed" data-element-ceiling="body" data-element-floor=".article-wrap">
	<ul>
		<li>
